The course gives an overview of the development of the ideas of multicultural education in Estonia and in international perspective. Minority education models and various adaptation programmes in organising multilingual education are introduced. The main strategies of intercultural teaching and learning are discussed. The course will be held in web-based learning environment.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To acquire general overview about development of ideas and current problems of multicultural education in Estonian and worldwide context. To support teachers readiness to work in multicultural classroom.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After the course student:· knows general trends in development of multicultral education · knows main principles of multicultural curriculum and can apply them in teaching practice· can plan and manage learning and teaching process  in multicultural classroom.
